longBusinessSummary: InterCard AG Informationssysteme, together with its subsidiaries, provides multifunctional card systems for universities, institutions of higher education, and other educational institutions in Germany and Switzerland. The company's multifunctional cards are used in providing access control to buildings, rooms, or laboratories; opening, closing, and paying for private storage facilities and lockers; recording time and attendance; managing printing jobs; making cashless payments for photocopies and scans; paying in the canteen, vending machines, or kiosks; and paying for washing and drying, as well as placing the tickets for public transport services. It also offers card accessories, such as card holders, clips, lanyards, and cases, as well as fasteners for card holders and cases. The company is based in Villingen-Schwenningen, Germany. InterCard AG Informationssysteme is a subsidiary of Sandpiper Digital Payments AG.
